1.how to create soft link/shortcut of any file
syntax==>ln -s source destination
example: ls -s /etc/hosts hosts_softlink
-------------------------------------------------
#################################################
-------------------------------------------------
2.how to create hard link of any file
syntax==>ln source destination
example: ln linkfile /root/home/
-------------------------------------------------
#################################################
-------------------------------------------------
3.how to find any file
locate cmd is very fast because it used the local database
syntax: locate file_name
example: locate vivek.txt
-------------------------------------------------
#################################################
-------------------------------------------------
4.update the database
syntax: updatedb
-------------------------------------------------
#################################################
-------------------------------------------------
5.how to find the file using find cmd 
syntax: find location-name file_name
exmaple:find /Desktop -name vps
-------------------------------------------------
#################################################
-------------------------------------------------
6.how to find a perticular find using by the specific user under any group
syntax: find location -user user_name -group group_name
example: find /home -user vps -group sales
-------------------------------------------------
#################################################
-------------------------------------------------
7. how to show contant of any file
syntax: cat filename
example: cat vivek.txt
-------------------------------------------------
#################################################
-------------------------------------------------
